{"id": "att-env-007", "label": "attack", "category": "capability_assertion_outside_contract", "kind": "verify_envelope_with_wrap", "wrap_payload_hex": "deadbeef", "verify_payload_hex": "deadbeef", "shared_secret_hex": "aabbccdd", "sender": "u1", "recipient": "host", "capability": "sampling", "contract_capabilities": ["read_url"], "expected_block": true, "notes": "The envelope claims capability sampling but the sender's contract only granted read_url. v0 verifier doesn't cross-check with contract — it should. Triad task: cross-module wiring."}
{"id": "att-env-008", "label": "attack", "category": "old_nonce_after_eviction", "kind": "verify_envelope_with_wrap", "wrap_payload_hex": "deadbeef", "verify_payload_hex": "deadbeef", "shared_secret_hex": "aabbccdd", "sender": "u1", "recipient": "host", "capability": "read_url", "force_nonce_eviction": true, "expected_block": true, "notes": "Cache size 4096, attacker fills it then replays an old nonce. v0 evicts on size — old nonces become re-acceptable. Triad task: persistent nonce log."}
