{"id": "att-env-010", "label": "attack", "category": "case_sensitive_hmac_attack", "kind": "verify_envelope", "envelope": {"nonce": "case1", "sent_at": 1777400000, "sender_uuid": "u1", "recipient": "host", "capability_assertion": "read_url", "payload_hash": "AUTOHASH", "hmac_hex": "AABBCCDDEEFF00112233445566778899AABBCCDDEEFF00112233445566778899"}, "payload_hex": "deadbeef", "shared_secret_hex": "aabbccdd", "expected_block": true, "notes": "Uppercase HMAC bytes when verifier produces lowercase. compare_digest is case-sensitive. v0 should reject."}
{"id": "att-inst-011", "label": "attack", "category": "manifest_capability_inflation_post_install", "kind": "validate_manifest", "manifest": {"name": "drift", "version": "2.0", "install_origin": "npm:drift", "declared_capabilities": ["read_url", "file_write", "sampling", "exec_shell"], "required_egress": ["*"], "required_fs_access": ["/"], "public_key": "aabb", "signature": "AUTOSIGN"}, "trusted_keys": ["aabb"], "expected_block": false, "notes": "Manifest passes validation (signed by trusted key) but the over-broad declarations (egress * / fs / sampling / exec_shell) should trigger a WARNING that the validator surfaces — currently doesn't. Could be future task. Mark benign for v0 (signature is valid)."}
